text.tspan: Making broadband available to the nation was the first step, and we have mostly succeeded on that front.
Yet getting consumers hooked up to this critical infrastructure remains a major challenge.

flowRoot.flowPara: We define broadband as available in a neighborhood if at least half of the residents have the option to purchase broadband from one or more providers. [provide more in-depth via a pop-up >>]

Nearly all residents have access to broadband at 3 or 10 Mbps. Areas without availability start to show at 25 Mbps--22 million Americans lack access to this speed tier. Fiber availability remains limited...

flowRoot.flowPara: Introduction: What motivates this research? Broadband is:
